        combined response, and by <NUMEX TYPE="PERCENT">6%</NUMEX> in the pessimistic combined response by <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">2020</TIMEX>.
        The total number of infections averted through a combined response would be <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">29 million</NUMEX>
        over the period <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">2004 to 2020</TIMEX> if treatment enhances prevention, a benefit that is <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">ten</NUMEX> times
        greater than that of a strategy which focuses on treatment only, even with optimal
        assumptions, and <NUMEX TYPE="PERCENT">51%</NUMEX> greater than that of a strategy which focuses on (less effective)
